@thefirerises: if you wish to record the movie, go for it! However, there are at least two setback you should consider.

1) If 1.5 minutes of iPhone HD video takes up 250MB then 164 minutes takes up approx. 27GB. Therefore, you may want to consider lower resolution to fit in those 14GB (if that iPhone HD is 720p, you should be fine with 480p).

2) Better safe than sorry. See http://torrentfreak.com/movie-spy-cameras-attack-the-dying-art-of-camcorder-piracy-120426/ ... and make sure your cinema doesn't have such anti-piracy measures installed.

